                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2382: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Warren</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-01-19T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 19, 1922—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4. Your 7, January 17, 1 p.m.</p>
                <p>Inform Caldwell that the Department has not in mind any measures with respect to
                    the Chinese Eastern Railway which would involve the maintenance of foreign or
                    Russian troops in the concession zone.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
